text:
Tough time to be a Chipotle lover. I mean the whole "giant meat recalls" thing and now this? At least the queso cheese they introduced was pretty good?
You guys don't have a single clue, is clear!
I think my brain stopped working after I read about their new 'digital experience platform'? Can someone explain in 10 words or less please? 
It's a website to order food easier 
That... makes sense, I guess?
I love it when big companies talk like we're just supposed to get what they're saying without explanation. "Yeah, our digital experience platform will definitely increase brand engagement!" - No, dude, you just made that term up.
But hey, at least their efforts are headed in a positive direction 
Hereâ€™s some great content from the company:

"We're dedicated to building a culture of innovation that leverages technology"

*translate* 
We're going to make an app and hope for the best.

You feel me? Companies try way too hard to make themselves sound super intelligent when really, we all know what's going on?.

Can you summarize the article? 
Apparently Chipotle's introducing a new... thing to improve online ordering. It claims it'll boost customer experiences (doubtful) and their sales (idk).
